{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ice|prevnum=711|prev=Gourgeist|nextnum=713|next=Avalugg}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Bergmite\n|jname=カチコール\n|jtranslit=Kachikōru\n|tmname=Kachikohru\n|category=Ice Chunk\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Ice\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Own Tempo\n|ability2=Ice Body\n|abilityd=Sturdy\n|ndex=712\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=079\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|weight-lbs=219.4\n|weight-kg=99.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Monster\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|expyield=61\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=190\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=bergmite\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Bergmite\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'カチコール\'\'\' \'\'Kachikohru\'\') is an {{type|Ice}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Avalugg}} starting at [[level]] 37.\n\n==Biology==\nBergmite is a quadruped Pokémon with a white, round body and nubby legs. Its upper half is encased in a slightly transparent, pale blue chunk of ice. Its eyes, which are yellow with purple sclerae, are visible through the ice. The ice itself forms a large triangle with smaller spikes on its forehead and hind end. Bermite can create cold air, which is uses to repair chinks or cracks in its icy coating. This air reaches temperature as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit (-100 degrees Celsius) and can also be used to freeze enemies. Bergmite lives in herds on snowy mountain tops and can sometimes be found huddled on the back of an {{p|Avalugg}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Wulfric Bergmite.png|thumb|left|250px|Bergmite in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nFive Bergmite debuted in \'\'[[XY120|All Hail the Ice Battlefield!]]\'\', in the [[Snowbelle Gym]], under the ownership of [[Wulfric]]. These were used to greet Trainers when they arrived to battle the Snowbelle Gym. Wulfric later used one of the Bergmite during his [[rematch]] against {{Ash}}; it battled {{AP|Pikachu}}, but was defeated.\n\n===Minor appearances===\n{{-}}\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY120|Bergmite|Ash\'s Pokédex|Bergmite, the Ice Chunk Pokémon. Bergmite\'s body is covered with ice, which is used to protect against opponents. Its cracks are fixed with cold air.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Bergmite Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Bergmite in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn the {{chap|X & Y}}, a Bergmite appeared under the ownership of a female {{tc|Pokémon Ranger}} at the Mini-game Corner.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Bergmite (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=ice}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=079|label1=Mountain|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It blocks opponents\' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Using air of {{tt|-150 degrees Fahrenheit|-100 degrees Celsius}}, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=It blocks opponents\' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Using air of {{tt|-150 degrees Fahrenheit|-100 degrees Celsius}}, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n[[Category:Pokémon in the Galar Pokédex]]<!--\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=VIII|reg1=Galar|num1=???}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Sword|v2=Shield|entry=TBD}}\n|}\n|}-->\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=ice}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=X|v2=Y|t=FFF|area=[[Frost Ca