}}\n\n==Trivia==\n\n===Origin===\nBergmite appears to be based on an {{wp|iceberg}} or a {{wp|stalagmite}}. Bergmite may represent the tip of the iceberg, which is small compared to the submerged part.\n\n====Name origin====\nBergmite may be a combination of \'\'iceberg\'\', \'\'{{wp|mite}}\'\', and possibly \'\'{{wp|stalagmite}}\'\'.\n\nKachikohru may be a combination of かちかち \'\'kachikachi\'\' (onomatopoeic word for frozen stiff), 凍る \'\'kōru\'\' (to freeze), and コールド \'\'cold\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=ice|type2=ice\n|ja=カチコール \'\'Kachikohru\'\'|jameaning=Possibly from {{tt|かちかち \'\'kachikachi\'\'|onomatopoeic word for frozen stiff}}, {{tt|凍る \'\'kōru\'\'|to freeze}}, and \'\'cold\'\'\n|fr=Grelaçon|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|grêle|hail}}\'\', \'\'{{tt|grelotter|shivering}}\'\', and \'\'{{tt|glaçon|ice}}\'\'\n|es=Bergmite|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Arktip|demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|Arctic|Arktis}}\'\' and \'\'Tip\'\'\n|it=Bergmite|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=꽁어름 \'\'Kkong\'eoreum\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|꽁꽁 \'\'kkong\'kkong\'\'|frozen hard}} and {{tt|얼음 \'\'eol\'eum\'\'|ice}}\n|zh_yue=冰寶 \'\'Bīngbóu\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|冰 \'\'bīng\'\'|ice}} and {{tt|寶寶 \'\'bóubóu\'\'|baby}}\n|hi=बर्गमाइट \'\'Bergmite\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Бергмайт \'\'Bergmayt\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ice|prevnum=711|prev=Gourgeist|nextnum=713|next=Avalugg}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Arktip]]\n[[es:Bergmite]]\n[[fr:Grelaçon]]\n[[it:Bergmite]]\n[[ja:カチコール]]\n[[zh:冰宝]]'}